   Ãƒâ€º Plot Outline:

        During the U.S. Civil War a group of criminals impersonating 
        soldiers unleash a powerful evil when they take refuge in an 
        abandoned house after robbing a bank. Isolated and presumed 
        deserted, the house is anything but safe...

        As night wears on and a thunderstorm grows outside, some members 
        of the group begin to have visions of mangled bodies and demonic 
        children while others hear equally disturbing things like voices
        deep within a well or faint clawing noises behind locked doors.

        Fear and paranoia grow as supernatural forces in the house start
        to manifest and people begin to die mysteriously causing the 
        group turn on each other. Driven by panic and mortal fear, plans
        of escape are made - but will the evil haunting them allow it?   

   Ãƒâ€º Our Two Cents Worth:                                                 

        Though there seem to be a fair amount of people out there with
        less than complimentary opinions of Dead Birds, it scared the 
        shit out of us! That said, we hope you enjoy the movie even 
        half as much as we did. If you do, let others know!!!   

        Director Alex Turner has made a near perfect example of what
        modern horror can and should be, but he didn't do it alone. A 
        chilling original screenplay by Simon Barrett (an admitted 
        Ring fan) is captured through stylish camera work from Steve
        Yedlin who also makes the most effective use of shadow we have
        seen in years. Combined with convincing performances from the 
        cast all this makes for a great film sure to creep you out. 

        And we are not even going to mention 5 seconds of footage we 
        feel should be remembered right alongside Janet's shower scene.
        If it fails to freak you right the fuck out, check your pulse
        cause you might already be dead!

